Description: Egypt, pair of crumbling stone figures, Luxor. Representing adult male and female, "Rameses and wife". Surrounded by stone walls bearing hieroglyphs. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Curator's comments: Female statue may have been defaced in ancient times. J M Hudson, 27/01/1998. Circumstances: The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
